@jakobgager Yeah, imagemagick and ciarosvg both rasterize the svg prior to conversion (loss of nice vector art data).  The act of pulling the svg back into the nb may seem wonky, but I had two things in mind
1. The extract fig transformer should not have to know about the converter at all.  The converter should not know about the extract fig transformer at all.
2. The notebook in memory **should** be a copy of the notebook just used during the export process (and can be modified freely).  I will double check that this is the case, but it most definitely is for from_filename and from_filestream cases.

@Carreau Sure, I'll add that back for you.  Also, don't forget if you want you can use the public _register_filter_ and _register_transformer_ methods (which are still there).  It wont be an issue to add it to the _export_....()_ convenience methods since they all use *_kw now, I'll just add it to the final method (_export()*).

@ivanov :see_no_evil:  My poor tests branch has been collecting dust for a week now :cry:

@ivanov @fperez 

Here's a small diagram I drew that tries to illustrate how nbconvert works (almost what you asked for on Thursday)
![nbconvert_process](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/3292874/795084/b9384964-ecda-11e2-8fab-b7dfc9ce70db.png)

@dpsanders Your notebook appears to have the figures embedded in html cells.  There is no way for nbconvert to parse the html and extract the images from the html (out of scope).  It renders because the end target is a web browser.

@Carreau `ipython nbconvert` without args displays help if there isn't a config file loaded that specifies notebooks.  Otherwise `ipython nbconvert` converts the notebooks in the _notebooks_ list.  We decided against `ipython nbconvert <directory>` in favor of `ipython nbconvert *.ipynb`

I'm okay talking more about the figures / keys, either tomorrow in the video meeting or next week in person.  I was on the fence about that (because of the Win/Nix line ending problem), but @ellisonbg strongly preferred not to have a binary/text subkey and now that it's implemented that way it doesn't bother me.
